name: application of plant protection product, by field sprayer | application of plant protection product, by field sprayer | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/24590/documentation

This dataset represents the application of protection product in one hectare (ha). In this operation occurs the application of herbicides, fungicides and insecticides. Functional Unit (FU) is one hectare of application of plant protection product. The operation time is about 0.11 hours per ha. However, only 62.5% of this time is spent performing the operation, the remaining fraction is time for maintenance, waiting in the field and re-allocations between the field plots.;Dataset exchanges scaled from GLO dataset based on diesel consumption in Canada. Created to proxy farm machinery/fieldwork representative of the Canadian context.

From agricultural field foreseen to be processed.

This activity ends with agrochemical applied. The dataset includes the diesel fuel consumption (5.77 L diesel per hour of effective operation) and the amount of agricultural machinery and shed. Also taken into consideration is the amount of emissions to the air from diesel combustion and the emission to the soil from tyre abrasion during the work process.
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/01:Crop and animal production, hunting and related service activities/016:Support activities to agriculture and post-harvest crop activities/0161:Support activities for crop production

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Most of the data used to modelling this activity were collected in the last few years (2012-2014). Diesel consumption data refer to year of 2019.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: This activity is performed with a tractor (power 75 hp; weight 2880 kg) and a boom spayer (weight 1730 kg; width 18 m). Life spam of the tractor is considered as 13500 operating hours and of the implement as 10000 operating hours. Machinery used, fuel consumption and operation efficiencies were based on data from sugarcane mills in Brazil, expert's informations and unpublished data.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Extrapolated from Brazilian data, uncertainty adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: The main source of data for agricultural inputs and operations modelling procedures is detailed in Cavalett et al., 2016. Emissions from the agricultural process are estimated according to Nemecek and Kagi, 2007.
